1. Task: Perform thorough QA testing of https://clyntro.com, exploring all pages and features, and generate comprehensive test cases documenting functionality, bugs, and user flows.. 
2. Hints(Optional): 
WEBSITE CREDENTIALS:
email: saurabh.rai@oyesense.com
Password: Admin@12345

TESTING OBJECTIVES:
- Thoroughly explore EVERY single page and feature of clyntro.com - no exceptions
- Generate at least 25 detailed test cases covering all major functionality
- Document any bugs or issues found with clear steps to reproduce
- Test navigation, forms, business logic, error handling, and edge cases
- Organize test cases by feature or functional area

EXPLORATION APPROACH:
1. Visit the site and thoroughly analyze the landing page structure
2. Log in using the provided credentials
3. Map out the entire site structure, identifying all major sections
4. Methodically explore each section in depth
5. For each feature, perform multiple tests covering different scenarios
6. Document all features, flows, and potential edge cases
7. Verify every form, button, link, and interactive element
8. Test all user roles and permissions if applicable

CRITICAL GUIDELINES:
- If the website happens to be about testing or QA, don't confuse the test cases YOU are creating with any test cases shown as CONTENT on the website
- Treat any testing-related content as regular content to be tested
- You must explore at least 15 different pages/sections before considering complete
- Generate test cases for at least 10 different features
- Test at least 5 different forms or interactive components
- Use both valid and invalid inputs for thorough testing
- Document each test case with: ID, summary, feature, preconditions, steps, and expected results
- Include test cases for both positive and negative scenarios
- Assign severity levels (High/Medium/Low) to any bugs found
- If you perform the same action 2 times without progress, try a different approach
- Before submitting forms, identify and fill ALL required fields first
- For better coverage, look for both common paths and edge cases

COMPLETION CRITERIA:
You may ONLY mark the task as complete when you have:
1. Explored at least 15 different pages/sections
2. Generated at least 25 detailed test cases
3. Tested at least 10 different features
4. Tested at least 5 different forms or interactive components
5. Documented any bugs or issues found
6. Verified all major navigation paths work correctly
